create_time.description: The timestamp of when the featureOnlinestore was created in RFC3339 UTC "Zulu" format, with nanosecond resolution and up to nine fractional digits.

effective_labels.description: All of labels (key/value pairs) present on the resource in GCP, including the labels configured through Terraform, other clients and services.

feature_online_store.description: The name of the FeatureOnlineStore to use for the featureview.

labels.description: A set of key/value label pairs to assign to this FeatureView. **Note**: This field is non-authoritative, and will only manage the labels present in your configuration. Please refer to the field 'effective_labels' for all of the labels present on the resource.

name.description: Name of the FeatureView. This value may be up to 60 characters, and valid characters are [a-z0-9_]. The first character cannot be a number.

region.description: The region for the resource. It should be the same as the featureonlinestore region.

terraform_labels.description: The combination of labels configured directly on the resource and default labels configured on the provider.

update_time.description: The timestamp of when the featureOnlinestore was last updated in RFC3339 UTC "Zulu" format, with nanosecond resolution and up to nine fractional digits.

entity_id_columns.description: Columns to construct entityId / row keys. Start by supporting 1 only.

uri.description: The BigQuery view URI that will be materialized on each sync trigger based on FeatureView.SyncConfig.

block.description: Configures how data is supposed to be extracted from a BigQuery source to be loaded onto the FeatureOnlineStore.

project_number.description: The project number of the parent project of the feature Groups.

feature_ids.description: Identifiers of features under the feature group.

block.description: List of features that need to be synced to Online Store.
Configures the features from a Feature Registry source that need to be loaded onto the FeatureOnlineStore.

cron.description: Cron schedule (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cron) to launch scheduled runs. To explicitly set a timezone to the cron tab, apply a prefix in the cron tab: "CRON_TZ=${IANA_TIME_ZONE}" or "TZ=${IANA_TIME_ZONE}".

block.description: Configures when data is to be synced/updated for this FeatureView. At the end of the sync the latest featureValues for each entityId of this FeatureView are made ready for online serving.
